{
  "doc_id": "39584",
  "text": "In the previous reviews on interventions for family caregivers, conflicting results were reported. For example, [CITATION_1] found that multicomponent interventions significantly reduce caregiver burden. However, [CITATION_2] found non-significant effects for burden, depression and well-being for family caregivers. These reviews included studies with varied level of evidence and, therefore, were unable to provide bias-free results. The results of our current review included studies with high level of evidence and evaluated the effects of multicomponent interventions on four important outcomes of burden, depression, health and social support. The current review also employed objective scientific methods that followed the PRISMA guideline in the selection of RCTs. This review with meta-analysis enables a comprehensive and updated overview on the effectiveness of multicomponent interventions for family caregivers and provides trustworthy results.",
